modules.description: Performs fuzzy string comparison using configurable rules to determine if two strings match approximately. It operates on string values and applies customizable evaluation criteria such as case sensitivity or partial matching. Useful for matching user input against known values with leniency, such as command aliases or search queries.

Implements approximate equality checks for values of type `M.t` using customizable thresholds and comparison logic. It supports numeric or comparable data types defined by the `M` module, such as floats or custom scalar types. Useful for testing or validation scenarios where exact equality is impractical, like comparing floating-point results with tolerance.

Implements approximate equality checks for numeric or comparable types using customizable thresholds and comparison logic. Supports operations like fuzzy string matching with configurable rules for case sensitivity or partial matches. Useful for testing floating-point results or matching user input with leniency, such as command aliases or search queries.
